---
title: Meatball Pho with Rice Noodles
description: This classic Vietnamese soup will warm your belly this winter. In our version, we’ve added little Asian-spiced beef meatballs. Garlic, ginger, and mint create a fragrant broth, and bok choy adds a splash of color. Have your own chopsticks? Now's the time to use them to slurp up all those delicious rice noodles!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54d21f936ced6e52798b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/54d21f936ced6e52798b4567.pdf
cuisine: Vietnamese
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 572 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  protein: 28 g
  fiber: 3 g
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/meatball-pho-54d21f936ced6e52798b4567
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping white and green parts separate. Peel the
@ginger{1%thumb} with a #spoon{} and then mince or grate along with the
@garlic{2%cloves}. Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Thinly slice the
@baby bok choy{2} leaves and stems. Coarsely chop the @mint{1%sprig}. Seed and
mince the @jalapeño{1}.

Heat @vegetable oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #pot over medium heat. Add half the
scallion whites and half the ginger and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.
Add the @pho stock concentrate{1} and @water{4%cups}. Bring to a boil, reduce to
a simmer, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, combine @ground beef{8%ounces} with garlic,
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining ginger, remaining scallion whites, and a
large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Add as much jalapeño as you
dare. Combine and form the mixture into bite-sized meatballs (about the size of
a ping-pong ball).

Heat @vegetable oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a pan over medium heat. Add the
meatballs and cook, rotating, until browned on all sides.

Add the meatballs, 1/3 of the @rice noodles{1%pack}, and bok choy to the broth.
Simmer until the noodles are tender and meatballs are cooked through, about
~{4%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> This classic Vietnamese soup will warm your belly this winter. In our version,
> we've added little Asian-spiced beef meatballs. Garlic, ginger, and mint create
> a fragrant broth, and bok choy adds a splash of color. Have your own
> chopsticks? Now's the time to use them to slurp up all those delicious rice
> noodles!